Description: Very hard to find late 60s/Early 70s Kay Telecaster, top of the line model. So rare I don’t see a single demo on youtube for anything like this model. C shaped neck. All original and in excellent shape given that it’s 50ish years old. Some expected wear and tear – scratches and dings - as shown in the photos but still a super solid, well-made guitar. Plays and sounds excellent. Electronics all work, with vintage sounding original pickups – very clean sound when clean and growls with overdrive. Factory working truss rod, straight neck, low action. Adjustable roller bridge. Comes with well-fitted hard shell twill case in perfect condition. Ships to the continental 48 states.
